
Pope_Benedict_XIII
instance
Pope Benedict XIII (Latin: Benedictus XIII; 2 February 1649 â€“ 21 February 1730), born Pietro Francesco Orsini, O.P., was Pope from 29 May 1724 to his death in 1730. He took the name of Vincenzo Maria Orsini when he became a Dominican friar. In the process towards sainthood, his cause for canonization opened in 1755, but it was soon closed. It was re-opened on 21 February 1931, but it was closed once again in 1940. It was opened once more on 17 January 2004, with the official process commencing in 2012. He now has the posthumous title of Servant of God.
